%p
  Assume that you are already using the albinochipmunk gemset.
%pre.code
  :preserve
    $ rvm gemset use albinochipmunk
    Now using gemset 'albinochipmunk'
%p
  And that you now wish to switch back to using the default gems directory for the currently selected ruby.
%p
  You can accomplish this using gemset clear:
%pre.code
  :preserve
    $ rvm gemdir
    /Users/wayne/.rvm/gems/1.9.2-head@albinochipmunk
    $ rvm gemset clear
    gemset cleared.
    $ rvm gemdir
    /Users/wayne/.rvm/gems/1.9.2-head

